uter does. This doesn't mean that the program gets deleted, all it means is that it doesn't automatically startup when your comp does as to slow down your comp and use up precious resources. You can actually uncheck everything except for CTFMON for I think that one is needed for the comp to run (this may be slightly different in Win98 for there may be a couple more important things as not to touch). I think in 98 the systray, and... ummm. if explorer is in there and anything else that looks important may be needed. You can always do a trial and error. If you run into trouble and need to go back but your comp won't start don't panic. You can always startup in &quot;safe mode&quot;. To do this you can keep tapping the &quot;F8&quot; key when your comp boots up till you get a boot selection screen. select safe mode and the rest should be self explanitory. Now Back to you Bryan. The other tab that may interest you, but holds many system files, would be the Tab labled &quot;Services&quot; in the system config utility. These also get loaded when your comp boots but they tend to be important. they can control many things that you need and use but a lot are just to control useless items. Use sense and common sense or trial and error. Hopefully this helps you out some. Now onto your annoying popups. A good tool that will get rid of Spyware on your comp that can be a source of your popups is <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://download.com.com/redir?pid=10121984&amp;merid=69274&amp;mfgid=69274&amp;ltype=dl_dlnow&amp;lop=link&amp;edId=3&amp;siteId=4&amp;oId=3000-2094-10121984&amp;ontId=2094&amp;dlrs=1&amp;destUrl=%2F3001-2094-10121984.html" target="top">ADAWARE</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->. Adaware is freeware and a good tool. Spyware comes packaged with manythings so don't be suprized to see it find a lot of spyware on your comp. BAD KAZAA. Also, to help you combat those terrible popups you can get <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://downloads-zdnet.com.com/redir?pid=10170069&amp;merid=73920&amp;mfgid=73920&amp;ltype=dl_dlnow&amp;lop=link&amp;edId=2&amp;siteId=2&amp;oId=3000-2366-10170069&amp;ontId=2366&amp;destUrl=%2F3001-2366-10170069.html" target="top">POPUP STOPPER</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->! This will stop all popups from coming to your computer. Note: Sometimes you want popups. Sometimes a site will have a link that takes you somewhere via popup. There is an option to quickly shut this off and turn it back on for those times. This is also a bit of good freeware offered online. Hope this helps you out. Lemme know how it works out for you. From your friendly GUMBY!  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bgumbyfunkdiscussion.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gumbyfunker>Gumbyfunker</A> at: 2/4/03 5:11:40 pm<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/fgumbyfunkdiscussionfrm8.showPrevMessage?topicID=2.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <br><br><a self href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fgumbyfunkdiscussionfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=1><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/addReply1.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fgumbyfunkdiscussionfrm8.emailToFriend?topicID=2.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fgumbyfunkdiscussionfrm8.threadControl?topicID=2.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/deleteThreadFire.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fgumbyfunkdiscussionfrm8.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of 